{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, for future work, we commit to conducting more comprehensive evaluations on safety, harmfulness, and bias to enhance the robustness and ethical standards of language model alignment.",
    "Gathering a high-quality dataset of sufficient scale is imperative to study various properties of current offline preference learning algorithms.",
    "There are many open-source preference labeled datasets available online, including Ultrafeedback (Cui et al., 2023), TLDR-Preferences (Stiennon et al., 2020a), and Nectar (Banghua et al., 2023).",
    "However, they show significant differences in 1) the quality and diversity of the prompts, 2) models used to generate the responses, 3) judge models, and 4) the number of preference pairs.",
    "It is therefore unclear which dataset is of sufficient quality to train a model on, and how the model's performance changes on downstream benchmarks."
  ]
}